            <span class="font-mono text-xs text-mute font-normal">02.</span>
            <span>Game where you merge fruit?</span>
          </span>
          <span class="text-mute group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform duration-200">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 256 256">
              <path d="M216.49,104.49l-80,80a12,12,0,0,1-17,0l-80-80a12,12,0,0,1,17-17L128,159l71.51-71.52a12,12,0,0,1,17,17Z"></path>
            </svg>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-5 pb-5 text-body text-xs md:text-sm leading-relaxed border-t border-hairline/50 pt-4">
          <p>
            Yes! If you are looking for the <strong>game where you merge fruit</strong>, you are in the right place! It is a physics-based puzzle match game. In this game, players drop various fruits into a container, combining matching pairs (such as two grapes or two oranges) to evolve them into larger fruits until they reach the final stage: a giant watermelon.
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- FAQ Item 3 -->
      <details class="group border border-hairline bg-canvas hover:border-hairline-strong transition-all duration-200 rounded-lg">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-5 cursor-pointer font-sans font-semibold text-sm md:text-base text-ink select-none list-none [&::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden">
