        <div class="px-5 pb-5 text-body text-xs md:text-sm leading-relaxed border-t border-hairline/50 pt-4">
          <p>
            Playing the <strong>fruit merge match game</strong> involves dropping colorful fruits into a box and matching identical pairs. As you drop each fruit, gravity and physics will cause them to bounce and roll. When two identical fruits touch, they combine into a single, larger fruit. The matching sequence progresses from tiny cherries to strawberries, grapes, and eventually a watermelon.
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- FAQ Item 7 -->
      <details class="group border border-hairline bg-canvas hover:border-hairline-strong transition-all duration-200 rounded-lg">
